title: THURSDAY 1/28 - Texans tag their man
itunes:title: THURSDAY 1/28 - Texans tag their man
description:
The final head coaching job has been filled (:07) as David Culley will become the new head coach of the Texans. Speaking of coaches, Bruce Arians looking to become the oldest head coach to ever win a Super Bowl, but if he does will it be his last? (1:12). Drew Brees' (1:59) future is still up in the air, so what does Saints GM Mickey Loomis plan to do if Brees retires? (2:13) Jets head coach talks about the future of Sam Darnold in New York (2:47) and Jennifer King (3:49) breaking down barriers in Washington. Plus, Lions wide receiver Kenny Golladay stops by the breakfast table
